## Project Title

Home Automation System using Bluetooth (HC-05) and Arduino

## Objectives

To control home appliances like light and fan using a smartphone via Bluetooth technology

## Working Principle

Mobile app sends ON/OFF command → HC-05 Bluetooth receives data → Arduino processes signal → Relay switches the device.

##  Circuit Connections

HC-05 to Arduino

- VCC → 5V
- GND → GND
- TX → RX (Pin 0)
- RX → TX (Pin 1)
- Relay Module to Arduino
- VCC → 5V
- GND → GND
- IN → Pin 8

##  Load (Bulb/Fan)

- Connected through relay COM and NO terminals

##  Components Required

- Arduino Uno
- HC-05 Bluetooth Module
- Relay Module (1 channel)
- LED bulb / fan (demo load)
- Jumper wires
- Breadboard
- 5V power supply
- Android smartphone

##  Applications

- Smart home automation
- College mini project
- Industrial control system
- IoT learningbase

## Result

The system successfully controls home appliances wirelessly using a smartphone via Bluetooth.
